# Writing RKstack Skills

This skill teaches how to create skills for the **rkstack plugin**. It combines three sources:

1. **This file** — our gstack-based design: templates, tiers, resolvers, build workflow
2. **refs/** — official Claude Code documentation (auto-updated from Anthropic every 3 hours)
3. **Companion files** — superpowers testing methodology for bulletproofing skills

When you need authoritative detail on a Claude Code feature, this file tells you exactly which ref to read and which section matters.

**Announce at start:** "I'm using the writing-rkstack-skills skill to create/edit a skill."

---

## RKstack Template System

We use a build system adapted from gstack. Human authors write `.tmpl` files; `gen-skill-docs.ts` resolves placeholders and produces the final `SKILL.md` that Claude reads at load time.

```
skills/{name}/SKILL.md.tmpl         <- human writes template + {{PLACEHOLDERS}}
scripts/gen-skill-docs.ts           <- reads .tmpl, resolves placeholders, writes .md
skills/{name}/SKILL.md              <- generated, committed, tagged AUTO-GENERATED
```

**Never edit SKILL.md directly.** Always edit the `.tmpl`. The generated file is overwritten on next build.

### File Layout

```
skills/{name}/
  SKILL.md.tmpl         # human-authored template (source of truth)
  SKILL.md              # generated output (committed, read by Claude)
  companion-file.md     # hand-authored reference (not templated)
  bin/                  # hook scripts (if skill has PreToolUse hooks)
```

Claude Code supports a directory per skill with SKILL.md as the entrypoint and any number of supporting files. Keep SKILL.md under 500 lines — move detailed reference material to separate files.

> **Full supporting files guidance:** Read `refs/skills.md` — section "Add supporting files".

