## Frontmatter

Every `.tmpl` starts with YAML frontmatter. We use a superset of the official Claude Code fields.

### RKstack-Required Fields

```yaml
---
name: skill-name-with-hyphens
preamble-tier: 2
version: 1.0.0
description: |
  Use when [specific triggering conditions].
  Third person. Under 500 characters. Max 1024 total.
allowed-tools:
  - Bash
  - Read
  - AskUserQuestion
---
```

- `name` — letters, numbers, hyphens only (max 64 chars). Gerund form preferred (`writing-plans`, `requesting-code-review`).
- `preamble-tier` — integer 1-4, controls preamble depth (see Preamble Tier Guide).
- `version` — semver string.
- `description` — starts with "Use when..." or action verbs. Describes ONLY triggering conditions, NOT the skill's workflow. This is critical: Claude reads descriptions to decide which skills to load. If the description summarizes the workflow, Claude may follow the description shortcut instead of reading the full skill. Keep it about WHEN, not WHAT.
- `allowed-tools` — tools Claude can use without permission prompts when this skill is active.

### Optional Fields

- `hooks` — PreToolUse hooks scoped to this skill's lifecycle.
- `benefits-from` — list of skills this skill may invoke or reference.

### Full Official Field Reference

Claude Code supports additional fields we don't currently use but may adopt:

| Field | What it does |
|-------|-------------|
| `disable-model-invocation` | Prevents Claude from auto-loading this skill. User-only invocation. |
| `user-invocable` | Set `false` to hide from `/` menu. Claude can still load it. |
| `context` | Set `fork` to run in a subagent context (isolated, no conversation history). |
| `agent` | Which subagent type to use with `context: fork` (`Explore`, `Plan`, custom). |
| `model` | Override model per skill. |
| `effort` | Override effort level (`low`, `medium`, `high`, `max`). |
| `paths` | Glob patterns — auto-activate only when working with matching files. |
| `argument-hint` | Autocomplete hint shown in `/` menu (e.g., `[issue-number]`). |

> **Complete field reference with defaults and types:** Read `refs/skills.md` — section "Frontmatter reference".

