## Preamble Tier Guide

The preamble is a bash block injected at the top of every generated SKILL.md via the `{{PREAMBLE}}` placeholder. It runs first, collecting project context (tech stack via scc, git branch, repo mode, CLAUDE.md presence). Higher tiers include everything from lower tiers.

| Tier | What It Adds | Use For |
|------|-------------|---------|
| **T1** | Core: scc detection, branch, repo-mode, framework hints, CLAUDE.md check, completion status + escalation | Lightweight utility skills (careful, freeze, guard, unfreeze, using-rkstack) |
| **T2** | T1 + AskUserQuestion format (re-ground → simplify → recommend → options) + Completeness principle (effort table, X/10 scoring) | Moderate workflow skills (brainstorming, debugging, plans, verification) |
| **T3** | T2 + Repo ownership (solo vs collaborative handling) + Search Before Building (three-layer knowledge model) | Heavy workflow skills needing repo context (TDD) |
| **T4** | Same as T3 | Gate-quality skills (requesting-code-review, finishing-a-development-branch) |

**Choosing a tier:**
- Asks the user questions → T2+ (needs AskUserQuestion format)
- Modifies code and needs repo ownership context → T3+
- Simple guard or reference → T1

AskUserFormat, Completeness, Escalation, and RepoMode are **sections within the preamble** — not separate `{{PLACEHOLDER}}`s. This matches gstack's design.

