## Plugin Structure

RKstack is a Claude Code plugin. The plugin system uses namespace isolation: skills are invoked as `/rkstack:skill-name`, preventing conflicts with other plugins or project-local skills.

```
rkstack/
  .claude-plugin/plugin.json    # manifest (name, version, description)
  skills/                       # plugin skills (shipped to users)
  hooks/                        # plugin hooks (hooks.json + scripts)
  agents/                       # agent definitions
```

Two environment variables are available in hook commands:
- `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}` — path to the plugin directory
- `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA}` — persistent data directory (survives plugin updates)

> **Plugin manifest schema and structure:** Read `refs/plugins.md` and `refs/plugins-reference.md`.

