## Subagents

We use subagents for isolated task execution (code-reviewer agent) and for delegating work in subagent-driven-development.

Agent definitions live in `agents/` as markdown files with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
name: code-reviewer
description: |
  Use this agent when a major step needs review against plan and standards.
model: inherit
---

[system prompt body]
```

Subagents get their own fresh context — they do NOT inherit the parent conversation. Built-in agents: `Explore` (read-only), `Plan` (research-focused), `general-purpose` (full tools).

Skills can preload into subagents, and subagents support persistent memory, tool restrictions, and `maxTurns` limits.

> **Agent configuration schema and patterns:** Read `refs/sub-agents.md`.

