## Memory and Context

Skills run within Claude's context window. Context fills fast — performance degrades as it fills. Design skills to be focused and concise.

**CLAUDE.md** is the persistent instruction system. Loads from multiple levels: managed > project > user. Skills should reference CLAUDE.md for project-specific config (test commands, build commands), not duplicate it.

**Rules system** (`.claude/rules/`) organizes instructions by topic with optional `paths` glob patterns for conditional loading. Import syntax: `@path/to/file` expands other files.

**Auto memory** — Claude saves notes to `~/.claude/projects/<project>/memory/`. Machine-local, not shared. Don't rely on it in skills.

> **CLAUDE.md hierarchy, import syntax, rules system:** Read `refs/memory.md`.
> **Context management and compaction behavior:** Read `refs/how-claude-code-works.md` — section "The context window".

