## Permissions

Skills grant tool access via `allowed-tools` in frontmatter. This works within the user's permission system — deny rules still apply.

Permission precedence: **deny > ask > allow**. Rules are tool-specific with glob matching: `Bash(npm run *)`, `Read(src/**)`, `Agent(AgentName)`.

Permission modes: `default` (ask for everything), `acceptEdits` (skip file prompts), `plan` (read-only), `auto` (classifier-based).

> **Permission rule syntax and tool-specific rules:** Read `refs/permissions.md`.

