## Resolver System

Placeholders follow the pattern `{{NAME}}` (uppercase + underscores) and are resolved by functions in `scripts/resolvers/`.

| Placeholder | Resolver | What It Produces |
|-------------|----------|-----------------|
| `{{PREAMBLE}}` | `preamble.ts` | Tier-based preamble block |
| `{{TEST_FAILURE_TRIAGE}}` | `preamble.ts` | Test failure ownership analysis |
| `{{BASE_BRANCH_DETECT}}` | `utility.ts` | Dynamic main/master/develop detection |

### Adding a New Placeholder

1. Check how gstack does it in `.upstreams/gstack/scripts/resolvers/`
2. Create resolver function in `scripts/resolvers/`
3. Register in `scripts/resolvers/index.ts`
4. Use `{{PLACEHOLDER_NAME}}` in any `.tmpl`

The build system fails on unresolved placeholders — you'll catch mistakes immediately.

