## CSO: Claude Search Optimization

Claude reads skill descriptions to decide which to load. Optimize for discovery.

**Description = WHEN to use, NOT WHAT it does.** Testing revealed that workflow summaries in descriptions cause Claude to skip the full skill content.

```yaml
# BAD: summarizes workflow — Claude shortcuts the full skill
description: Dispatches subagent per task with code review between tasks

# GOOD: triggering conditions only
description: Use when executing implementation plans with independent tasks
```

**Keywords:** Use error messages, symptoms, synonyms, tool names Claude would search for.

**Token budget:** Descriptions are loaded into context so Claude knows what's available. Budget is 2% of context window (~16K chars). Many skills = some excluded. Run `/context` to check.

> **Skill discovery mechanics and troubleshooting:** Read `refs/skills.md` — section "Troubleshooting".

