## Contributor Checklist

- [ ] Edited `.tmpl` (not `.md`)
- [ ] `{{PREAMBLE}}` is first placeholder after frontmatter
- [ ] All required fields: name, preamble-tier, version, description, allowed-tools
- [ ] Description is triggering conditions only (no workflow summary)
- [ ] Tier chosen appropriately
- [ ] Checked gstack and superpowers upstreams
- [ ] No hardcoded framework commands
- [ ] SKILL.md under 500 lines (reference material in companion files)
- [ ] `just build` succeeds
- [ ] `just check` passes
- [ ] `just skill-check` shows green
- [ ] Tested with RED → GREEN → REFACTOR
- [ ] Committed both `.tmpl` and `.md`

---

## Anti-Patterns

- **Editing SKILL.md directly** — overwritten on next build
- **Workflow summary in description** — Claude shortcuts the full skill
- **Inventing patterns when gstack has one** — check `.upstreams/gstack/` first
- **Hardcoding project commands** — read from CLAUDE.md or ask the user
- **Separate placeholders for preamble content** — AskUserFormat, Completeness, RepoMode belong INSIDE the preamble
- **Narrative storytelling** — "In session 2025-10-03 we found..." is too specific
- **Multi-language dilution** — one excellent example beats five mediocre ones
- **Skills over 500 lines** — move reference material to companion files
